-- pg_turbovec v1.7.3 -- turbovec fork upgrade to v0.9.0.
--
-- This file is a *reference mirror*. The authoritative install
-- script is generated by `cargo pgrx schema`.
--
-- v1.7.3 upgrades the turbovec kernel from the v0.7.0-era fork
-- (6e80a59) to a fork rebased onto upstream turbovec v0.9.0
-- (d3d468e). The headline reason:
--
--   FIX: on x86_64 CPUs WITHOUT AVX2 (Intel Ivy Bridge / Sandy
--   Bridge Xeons, pre-2014), the old kernel's scalar fallback
--   read the perm0-interleaved SIMD code layout as if it were
--   sequential, returning silently-wrong / repeated top-k from
--   ORDER BY emb <=> probe LIMIT N. Upstream fixed this in
--   turbovec PR #108 (issue #106), released v0.8.0, with a
--   proper score_query_into_heap scalar fallback. CPUs with
--   AVX2/AVX-512/NEON were never affected.
--
-- The upgrade also brings (adopted but inert here):
--   - TQ+ per-coordinate calibration fields, constructed as
--     identity (empty) on the pg_turbovec relfile path, so they
--     have NO effect on recall or wire format in v1.7.3.
--     Persisting them for a recall gain is a future minor release
--     (wire-format VERSION 3 -> 4 + REINDEX).
--   - Security hardening: MAX_DIM=65536, NaN/Inf/huge-magnitude
--     rejection, checked-mul in the .tv/.tvim loaders.
--
-- The on-disk relfile format is byte-identical to v1.6.x / v1.7.x
-- (MetaPageData::version = 3). There is no DDL or on-disk
-- migration. The upgrade path `ALTER EXTENSION pg_turbovec UPDATE
-- TO '1.7.3';` resolves against this intentionally-empty file.
--
-- Affected users (pre-AVX2 x86_64) should upgrade to v1.7.3 and
-- can drop any `SET enable_indexscan = off;` workaround. No
-- REINDEX is needed -- the relfile bytes never changed; only the
-- scan-time kernel that reads them was wrong on pre-AVX2 CPUs.
